        "content": "<p>In <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/12056\">#12056</a> I introduce two lemmas on isomorphisms, this one and a similar lemma on the right:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">is_iso.of_is_iso_comp_left</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"bp\">∀</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">C</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">_inst_1</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">category</span> <span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span> <span class=\"n\">Z</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"bp\">⟶</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">g</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span> <span class=\"bp\">⟶</span> <span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hf</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">is_iso</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hfg</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">is_iso</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"bp\">≫</span> <span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">)],</span> <span class=\"n\">is_iso</span> <span class=\"n\">g</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(In a future PR, I plan to add similar results for equivalence of categories instead of isomorphisms.)</p>",
